<eesti>M&auml;&auml;ruse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Regulation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) M&auml;&auml;rusega kehtestatakse kulude omistamise ja kulude arvestamise metoodika telefoni-, p&uuml;siliini- v&otilde;i sidumisteenuse turul olulise turuj&otilde;uga ettev&otilde;tjast &uuml;ldkasutatava telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu operaatori poolt, kes osutab telefoni-, p&uuml;siliini- v&otilde;i sidumisteenust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Regulation establishes the methodology of cost allocation and cost accounting in the market of telephone, leased lines and interconnection services by public telecommunications network operators with significant market power who provide the telephone, leased line or interconnection service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&auml;&auml;rus rakendub telefoni-, p&uuml;siliini- v&otilde;i sidumisteenuse turul "Telekommunikatsiooniseaduse" &sect; 8 kohaselt Sideameti poolt olulise turuj&otilde;uga ettev&otilde;tjaks (edaspidi OTE) tunnistatud &uuml;ldkasutatava telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu operaatori suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Regulation applies to public telecommunications network operators who have been declared as undertakings with significant market power by the Estonian National Communications Board pursuant to &sect; 8 of the Telecommunications Act in the telephone, leased line or interconnection services market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolev OTE poolt kulude arvestamise ja kulude omistamise metoodika (edaspidi metoodika) on koosk&otilde;las Euroopa Komisjoni soovitustega. (2) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) This methodology for cost accounting and cost allocation by the undertaking with significant market power (hereinafter methodology) is in conformity with the recommendations of the European Commission. (2) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Metoodika n&otilde;uded p&otilde;hinevad OTE erinevate &auml;rivaldkondade kulude arvestamise lahususel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The requirements of the methodology are based on the accounting separation principle of various business lines of an undertaking with significant market power. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruandluss&uuml;steemis peavad olema eristatud OTE erinevad &auml;rivaldkonnad, mis on defineeritud m&auml;&auml;ruse &sect; 2 l&otilde;ikes 4, sealhulgas tuleb ka eristada erinevaid kuluelemente seoses erinevate tegevustega, tagades transferthindade selguse ja kulup&otilde;hisuse. </eesti>
<inglise>The accounting system must distinguish between different business lines of an undertaking with significant market power which are defined in subsection 2 (4) of this Regulation; also cost components associated with various activities must be distinguished in order to guarantee the transparency and cost-orientation of transfer prices. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lisaks metoodika n&otilde;uetele tuleb OTE-l arvestada ka "Telekommunikatsiooniseaduse" &sect; 51 l&otilde;ike 7 alusel Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud p&uuml;siliini- ja sidumisteenuse tasude arvestamise metoodikat ja selle p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An undertaking with significant market power shall, in addition to the requirements of the methodology, observe the methodology and principles of calculating leased line and interconnection service charges established in subsection 51 (7) of the Telecommunications Act by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Metoodikas on toodud OTE kuluarvestuss&uuml;steemi v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamise &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tted. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The methodology provides the general principles for establishing the cost accounting system of an undertaking with significant market power. </inglise>
<eesti>Kulude omistamist puudutavate spetsiifiliste k&uuml;simuste &uuml;le peab otsustama OTE, konsulteerides vajaduse korral Sideametiga. </eesti>
<inglise>Specific issues in cost allocation shall be decided by the undertaking with significant market power who shall consult with the Estonian National Communications Board, if necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;lekandev&otilde;rk kuluarvestuse t&auml;henduses on telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu osa, mis &uuml;hendab telefonijaamu v&otilde;i juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rke ning mis algab signaali algatajale l&auml;hima telefoniv&otilde;rgus&otilde;lme tarbijaliidese v&auml;ljundis ja l&otilde;peb sama telefoniv&otilde;rgu signaali l&otilde;petava telefoniv&otilde;rgus&otilde;lme tarbijaliidese v&auml;ljundis v&otilde;i sidumispunktis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of cost accounting, a transmission network is the part of the telecommunications network which connects exchanges or local access networks and which starts at the output of the subscriber interface of the telephone network node closest to the signal originating exchange and ends at the output of the subscriber interface of the signal terminating exchange of the same network or at the interconnection point. </inglise>
<eesti>Tarbijaliidese tehniline m&otilde;iste on s&auml;testatud "Telekommunikatsiooniseaduse" &sect; 4 l&otilde;ike 5 alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktis. </eesti>
<inglise>The technical definition of the subscriber interface is provided for in the legislation established on the basis of subsection 4 (5) of the Telecommunications Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(03.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 35, 197) </eesti>
<inglise>(03.04.2001 entered into force 08.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 35, 197) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eriteenuste v&otilde;rk t&auml;hendab k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses mitte-&uuml;ldkasutatavat telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rku, mida kasutatakse eriteenuste osutamiseks ja millele esitatakse erin&otilde;udeid, nagu t&auml;iendavad turvan&otilde;uded, t&auml;iendavad operatiivsusn&otilde;uded jms ning millel on piiratud kasutus&otilde;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Regulation, special service network means a non-public telecommunications network which is used for providing special services and which is governed by specific requirements, such as additional security requirements, additional operational requirements, etc. and which has restricted right of use. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Faktooring on suunatud teenuste m&uuml;&uuml;jatele ning p&otilde;hineb v&otilde;lan&otilde;uete, mille makset&auml;htaeg ei ole veel saabunud, teatud tasu eest loovutamisel finantseerimisasutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Factoring means assigning debt securities the payment of which is not yet due to a financial institution for a certain fee, and is meant for service providers. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Omistatavad kulud t&auml;hendavad k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses otsekulusid, otseselt omistatavaid kulusid ja kaudselt omistatavaid kulusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Allocated costs are, for the purposes of this Regulation, direct costs, directly attributable costs and indirectly attributable costs. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Teenuse osutamine tarbijale (edaspidi jaem&uuml;&uuml;k) kui &auml;rivaldkond k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse t&auml;henduses on telefoniteenuse osutamine tarbijale. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) For the purposes of this Regulation, provision of services to the subscriber (hereinafter retail) as a business line is the provision of the telephone service to users. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellele valdkonnale omistatavad kulud sisaldavad &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rgu ja juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rgu kasutamise transferthindu, samuti tarbijaga seotud turunduse ja arvelduskulusid. </eesti>
<inglise>The costs allocated to retail include transfer charges related to the use of core network and local access network, and the marketing and billing costs associated with the subscriber. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) &Auml;rivaldkonnad k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse t&auml;henduses on &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rguga seotud teenuste osutamine, juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rguga seotud teenuste osutamine, teenuste osutamine tarbijale ja muud tegevused. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) For the purposes of this Regulation, business lines mean provision of services in connection with core network, local access network, provision of services to the subscribers (hereinafter retail) and other activities. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu l&otilde;pp-punkt (edaspidi l&otilde;pp-punkt) on telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt m&auml;&auml;ratletav punkt, kus on telekommunikatsiooniteenuse kasutajale loodud juurdep&auml;&auml;s v&otilde;i v&otilde;imalus juurdep&auml;&auml;suks telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgule. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A telecommunications network termination point (hereinafter termination point) is a physically defined telecommunications network point where users of telecommunications services are provided or can be provided with access to the telecommunications network </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rk kuluarvestuse t&auml;henduses on telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu osa l&otilde;pp-punkti ja sellele l&auml;hima telefonijaama vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Local access network for the purposes of cost accounting means the part of a telecommunications network between a termination point and the closest exchange. </inglise>
<eesti>Juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rk algab telefoniv&otilde;rgu l&otilde;pp-punktis asuva jaotusseadme tarbijapoolsetelt klemmidelt ja l&otilde;peb l&otilde;pp-punktile l&auml;hima telefoniv&otilde;rgus&otilde;lme tarbijaliidese v&auml;ljundklemmidel. </eesti>
<inglise>Local access network starts at the subscriber's distribution frame of the terminal point of the telephone network and ends at the output of the subscriber's interface of the telephone network node closest to the terminal point. </inglise>
<eesti>Jaotusseadme tehniline m&otilde;iste on s&auml;testatud "Telekommunikatsiooniseaduse" &sect; 4 l&otilde;ike 5 alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktis. </eesti>
<inglise>The technical definition of the distribution frame is provided for in the legislation established on the basis of subsection 4 (5) of the Telecommunications Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(03.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.08.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 35, 197) </eesti>
<inglise>(03.04.2001 entered into force 08.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 35, 197) </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Kuluk&auml;itur on p&otilde;hjuslik tegur, mis m&otilde;jutab kulusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Driver is a causal factor which affects costs. </inglise>
<eesti>Kuluk&auml;iturid jagunevad mahup&otilde;histeks ja tegevusp&otilde;histeks. </eesti>
<inglise>Drivers are volume or activity based. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Kulukogum (cost pool) on kulude grupp, mille k&auml;itumise m&auml;&auml;rab &uuml;ks ja sama kuluk&auml;itur. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) Cost pool is a group of costs the behaviour of which is determined by one and the same driver. </inglise>
<eesti>(11) Kuluarvestus jooksevhindades (current cost accounting - CCA) on kuluarvestusbaas kiiresti muutuva majanduskeskkonna jaoks, kui kuluarvestus ajaloolistes hindades (historical cost accounting - HCA) ei anna adekvaatseid tulemusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(11) Current Cost Accounting (CCA) is a cost base used for a fast changing economic environment if the historical cost accounting (HCA) fails to give adequate results. </inglise>
<eesti>(12) Muud tegevused on &auml;rivaldkond, kuhu kuuluvad k&otilde;ik &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud teenused, mis ei ole seotud &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rgus, juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rgus ega jaem&uuml;&uuml;gis osutatavate teenustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(12) Other activities means the business line which covers all other services which are not services provided in core network business, local access network business or retail business. </inglise>
<eesti>(13) Transferthind ehk &uuml;lekandmishind on arvestuslik hind teenuse osutamise eest ettev&otilde;ttesiseselt &uuml;helt majandus&uuml;ksuselt teisele majandus&uuml;ksusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(13) Transfer price or transfer value is an accountable value for providing a service within an undertaking by one economic unit to another economic unit. </inglise>
<eesti>(14) V&otilde;rguseadmed on telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu osad: &uuml;lekandes&uuml;steem koos selle juurde kuuluvate l&uuml;litusseadmetega, muud abis&uuml;steemid ja rajatised, mis v&otilde;imaldavad telekommunikatsiooniv&otilde;rgu kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud l&otilde;pp-punktide ja sidumispunktide vahel elektriliste v&otilde;i elektromagnetiliste signaalide edastamist kaabli kaudu, raadio, optiliste v&otilde;i muude vahenditega. </eesti>
<inglise>(14) Network component means parts of the telecommunications network: transmission system including switching equipment and other support systems and facilities which enable the transmission of electrical or electromagnetic signals between the defined network termination points or interconnection points by way of a cable, by radio, optical or other means. </inglise>
