<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Kulude omistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Allocation of costs </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Kulude omistamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Principles of allocation of costs </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kulude omistamise protsess peab p&otilde;hinema kulude p&otilde;hjusliku seose anal&uuml;&uuml;sil, mille alusel peab kulud omistama nendele teenustele ja toodetele, mis on p&otilde;hjustanud nende kulude tekkimise. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The process of cost allocation shall be based on the analysis of cost causation whereby the costs must be attributed to those services and products which have caused such costs. </inglise>
<eesti>Selleks peab kasutusele v&otilde;tma tegevusp&otilde;hise kuluarvestuse (activity based costing - ABC) printsiibid, mille n&auml;ide on toodud lisas 6. (2) P&otilde;hjuslikkuse n&otilde;ue kulude omistamisel n&otilde;uab OTE-lt kohase ja detailse kulude jaotamise metoodika kehtestamist oma kuluarvestuss&uuml;steemis, milleks on vaja: </eesti>
<inglise>The activity based costing (ABC) methodology must be used therefor; an example of that is given in Annex 6. (2) The cost causation requirement in cost allocation requires that the undertaking with significant market power establish a relevant and detailed cost allocation methodology in its cost accounting system whereby the undertaking with significant market power is required to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) iga kulu- ja tuluartikli ning kapitali kasutuse omistamise anal&uuml;&uuml;si; </eesti>
<inglise>1) perform cost allocation of every item of revenue, cost and capital employed; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;ituri m&auml;&auml;ratlemist, mis on aluseks kulude omistamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) determine the driver which is the basis for cost allocation: </inglise>
<eesti>3) m&auml;&auml;ratletud k&auml;ituri kasutamist kuluartiklite omistamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) use the determined driver in cost allocation; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kulude, mida ei ole v&otilde;imalik p&otilde;hjuslikkuse seosest l&auml;htuvalt omistada, koondamist eraldi kulukogumisse. </eesti>
<inglise>4) collect the costs which cannot be allocated according to the principle of causation, in separate cost pools. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kulude omistamisel peab j&auml;lgima kolme p&otilde;hiprintsiipi: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Three main principles must be observed in cost allocation: </inglise>
<eesti>1) selgus: OTE peab avaldama t&auml;iendatud versiooni oma kulude omistamise metoodikast, kui selles tehakse olulisi muudatusi. </eesti>
<inglise>1) transparency: the operator must publish a revised version of its cost allocation methodology when relevant changes are made thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>OTE teavitab muudatuste tegemisest Sideametit v&auml;hemalt 10 kalendrip&auml;eva ette; </eesti>
<inglise>The undertaking with significant market power shall inform the Estonian National Communications Board at least 10 days in advance of the making of the changes. </inglise>
<eesti>2) j&auml;rjepidevus: samu omistamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid tuleb kasutada aastast aastasse. </eesti>
<inglise>2) consistency: the same allocation principles must be used each year. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tehakse muudatusi, peab OTE &uuml;mber arvestama ka eelneva aasta aruanded uute p&otilde;him&otilde;tete alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>If changes are made, the undertaking with significant market power must calculate the accounts of the previous year according to the new principles; </inglise>
<eesti>3) olulisus: spetsiaalsete omistamisp&otilde;him&otilde;tete kasutamine ei ole vajalik, kui nende kasutamisest tulenev m&otilde;ju v&auml;ljundile ei ole oluline. </eesti>
<inglise>3) relevance: the use of special cost allocation principles is not necessary if the effect of those principles on output is not relevant. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Kulude liigitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Classification of costs </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kulud jagunevad mitme toote ja teenuse vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Costs are shared between different products and services. </inglise>
<eesti>Iga kuluartikkel kuulub &uuml;hte j&auml;rgmistest kategooriatest: </eesti>
<inglise>Each item of cost belongs to one of the following categories: </inglise>
<eesti>1) operatiivkulud ehk otsesed kulud (direct and directly attributable costs) on kulud, mida saab otse ja &uuml;heselt seostada mingi teenuse v&otilde;i tootega ning mis on kajastatud OTE aruandluss&uuml;steemis mingi toote v&otilde;i teenuse tootmiskuludena; 2) kaudselt omistatavad kulud (edaspidi kaudkulud) ehk tootmise &uuml;ldkulud (indirectly attributable costs), mille kohta kasutatakse ka terminit pool-otsekulud (semidirect costs), mille hulka kuuluvad ka &uuml;hiskulud (joint costs), on kulud, mida saab siduda teenuse v&otilde;i tootega, kasutades vastavat kuluk&auml;iturit; </eesti>
<inglise>1) direct and directly attributable costs are costs which can be directly and unambiguously attributed to a service or product and which are specified in the accounting system of the undertaking with significant market power as costs incurred in the production of a certain product or service; 2) indirectly attributable costs, also called semidirect costs, including joint costs are costs which can be related to a service or product by way of a driver. </inglise>
<eesti>3) adresseerimatud kulud (edaspidi &uuml;ldkulud) (unattributable costs) on kulud, mida ei saa toote v&otilde;i teenusega seostada ei otseselt ega kaudselt, mist&otilde;ttu neid kulusid ei saa omistada toodetele v&otilde;i teenustele p&otilde;hjuslikkuse seose alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) unattributable costs are costs which cannot be attributed to a product or service directly or indirectly, and therefor those costs cannot be allocated to products or services on the basis of the cost causation principle. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;ldkulud tuleb kuluaruandes selgelt identifitseerida ja esitada sama aruande eraldi kirjetel. </eesti>
<inglise>Unattributable costs must be clearly identified in the statement of costs and shall be presented in different entries of the same accounts. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;ldkulude omistamiseks toodetele ning teenustele kasutatakse peamiselt j&auml;rgmisi meetodeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following methods are mainly used for allocating unattributable costs to products and services. </inglise>
<eesti>1) brutotulu meetod - k&auml;ibe alusel omistamine, kus &uuml;ldkulud omistatakse teenustele vastavalt mingi teenuse k&auml;ibeosa proportsioonile koguk&auml;ibes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) gross income method is the allocation on the basis of turnover where unattributable costs are allocated to services on the basis of the share of the turnover of a certain service in the total turnover; </inglise>
<eesti>2) netotulu meetod - &uuml;ldkulud omistatakse toodetele ja teenustele vastavalt mingi teenuse panusele netotulusse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) net income method where unattributable costs are allocated to products and services on the basis of the share of a service in the net income; </inglise>
<eesti>3) jaotatavate kulude meetod - &uuml;ldkulud omistatakse jaotatavate kuludega* samas proportsioonis. </eesti>
<inglise>3) attributable cost method where unattributable costs are allocated in the same proportion as the attributable costs*. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Detailsete ja l&auml;bipaistvate teenuste omahinna kalkuleerimiseks peab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 2 nimetatud kaudkulusid omistama ABC p&otilde;him&otilde;tetest l&auml;htuvalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For the calculation of the cost value of detailed and transparent services, the indirectly attributable costs specified in clause (1) 2) of this section must be allocated on the basis of ABC principles. </inglise>
<eesti>ABC-l p&otilde;hineva kaudkulude omistamise printsiibid on toodud lisas 6. </eesti>
<inglise>The ABC principles of allocating indirectly attributable costs are set out in Annex 6. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 3 nimetatud &uuml;ldkulud peab omistama k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 punktis 3 esitatud jaotatavate kulude meetodil. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The unattributable costs specified in clause (1) 3) of this section shall be allocated on the basis of the attributed cost method specified in clause (2) 3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Kulude omistamise protsess </eesti>
<inglise>Process of cost allocation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kulude omistamisel peab l&auml;htuma lisas 1 toodud kulude omistamise etappidest, mida v&otilde;ib vajaduse korral detailiseerida. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The allocation of costs shall be based on the stages of cost allocation set out in Annex 1, which, if necessary, can be further specified. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kuluarvestuslik informatsioon, mis sisaldub kulu- ja finantsaruannetes, tuleb jaotada operatiivkulusid ja kapitalikulusid puudutavaks informatsiooniks ning raamatupidamiskirjeteks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Cost accounting information which is contained in cost accounting and financial reports must be divided into operating costs, capital cost and accounting entries. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kulusid peab omistama j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Costs must be allocated as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) telekommunikatsiooniteenustele omistatakse kulud, mida saab otseselt siduda konkreetse telekommunikatsiooniteenusega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) costs that can be directly associated with particular telecommunications services shall be allocated to such services; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&otilde;rgukomponentidele omistatakse kulud, mis seonduvad mitme teenusega, mis k&otilde;ik kasutavad antud v&otilde;rgukomponenti ning seet&otilde;ttu ei saa neid otse konkreetsele teenusele kanda; </eesti>
<inglise>2) costs that are associated with several services all of which use the particular network component and therefor cannot be attributed directly to a particular service shall be allocated to network components; </inglise>
<eesti>3) seotud funktsioonidele omistatakse erinevate funktsioonide t&auml;itmiseks sooritatavate tegevuste kulud, mis on vajalikud teenuse osutamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) costs of activities performed in connection with various functions which are necessary for the provision of services shall be allocated to the related functions; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muudele funktsioonidele omistatakse erinevate tegevuste kulud, mis ei ole seotud konkreetse teenuse osutamisega, kuid on olulised ettev&otilde;tte edasiseks funktsioneerimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) costs of various activities which are not related to the provision of particular services but are important for the operations of the undertaking shall be allocated to other functions. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kulude omistamine toimub j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Costs are allocated as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) muude funktsioonide t&auml;itmisega seotud kulude omistamine seotud funktsioonidele, v&otilde;rgukomponentidele ja teenustele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) costs related to the performance of other functions are allocated across related functions, network components and services; </inglise>
<eesti>2) seotud funktsioonide t&auml;itmisega tekkinud kulude omistamine v&otilde;rgukomponentidele ja teenustele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) costs related to the performance of related functions are allocated across network components and services; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&otilde;rgukomponentide kulude ja teenuste otsekulude omistamine teenustele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) network component costs and direct service costs are allocated to services; </inglise>
<eesti>4) erinevate teenuste kulude omistamine neljale &auml;rivaldkonnale - &uuml;lekandev&otilde;rgu&auml;rile, juurdep&auml;&auml;suv&otilde;rgu&auml;rile, jaem&uuml;&uuml;gile ja muudele tegevustele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) various service costs are allocated to the four business lines - core network, local access network, retail and other activities. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Operatiivkulude liigitus </eesti>
<inglise>Classification of operating costs </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Operatiivkulude liigitus on j&auml;rgmine: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The classification of operating costs is the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) amortisatsioon; </eesti>
<inglise>1) depreciation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) varustamise, paigaldamise ja hoolduskulud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) supply, installation and maintenance costs; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&otilde;rgu planeerimis- ja arenduskulud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) network planning and development costs; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&otilde;rgu juhtimiskulud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) network management costs; </inglise>
<eesti>5) marketingi- ja m&uuml;&uuml;gikulud; </eesti>
<inglise>5) marketing and sales costs; </inglise>
<eesti>6) faktooringu- ja inkassokulud; </eesti>
<inglise>6) factoring and collection costs; </inglise>
<eesti>7) operaatorteenuse kulud; </eesti>
<inglise>7) operator services costs; </inglise>
<eesti>8) teatmike v&auml;ljaandmisega seotud kulud; </eesti>
<inglise>8) directory services costs; </inglise>
<eesti>9) maksed teistele operaatoritele; </eesti>
<inglise>9) payments to other operators; </inglise>
<eesti>10) muud operatiivkulud. </eesti>
<inglise>10) other operating costs. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Lisas 2 kajastatakse eespool nimetatud operatiivkulusid, kohustuslikke meetodeid nende omistamiseks ja valdkondi, kuhu neid peab omistama. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Annex 2 contains the operating costs specified above, obligatory methods for cost allocation, and business lines which must be used in cost allocation. </inglise>
<eesti>Toodud jaotust v&otilde;ib vajaduse korral t&auml;iendada ja all-liigendada. </eesti>
<inglise>If necessary, the classification may be supplemented and further subdivided. </inglise>
