<eesti>Esimene etapp koosneb j&auml;rgmistest sammudest: </eesti>
<inglise>The first stage consists of the following steps: </inglise>
<eesti>1) homogeensete kulukogumite loomine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) formation of homogeneous cost pools; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kulukogumi m&auml;&auml;rade leidmine, mille k&auml;igus kulukogumi kulude maht omistatakse sobiva kuluk&auml;ituri mahuga ning saadakse kulukogumi m&auml;&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>2) determination of cost pool rates whereby the volume of costs of a cost pool are allocated to the volume of an appropriate driver and the cost pool rate is arrived at. </inglise>
<eesti>Teise etapi k&auml;igus omistatakse kulukogumid teenustele, mille aluseks v&otilde;etakse kulukogumi m&auml;&auml;r ja ressursside hulk kasutatuna iga teenuse poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>In the second stage, cost pools are allocated to services, whereas the cost pool rate and the amount of resources used for each service is used as the basis. </inglise>
<eesti>Kehtib seos: </eesti>
<inglise>There is a correlation: </inglise>
<eesti>Kaudkulu = kulukogumi m&auml;&auml;r &times; kuluk&auml;ituri maht. </eesti>
<inglise>Indirectly attributable costs = cost pool rate &times; volume of driver. </inglise>
